    "Impact of Pruning.",
    "When irrelevant entities in retrieved textual subgraphs are not pruned (w/o Soft Pruning), the performance on WebQSP is worse compared to the w/o Retrieval and w/o Graph Encoder variant.",
    "This suggests that pruning is crucial, especially in dense graphs, to improve the quality of graph tokens and avoid negative impacts from irrelevant entities.",
    "Importance of Text Attributes.",
    "When the text attributes of retrieved subgraphs are excluded, relying solely on the soft token does not enhance the generation process in graph-related tasks."
